{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":167058,"duration_api_ms":166976,"num_turns":3,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d54861f6-fade-470b-b846-074e530ae7a5","total_cost_usd":0.43056099999999997,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":28606,"cache_read_input_tokens":78150,"output_tokens":5253,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":28606,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4,"outputTokens":5253,"cacheReadInputTokens":78150,"cacheCreationInputTokens":28606,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.3492075,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":56,"outputTokens":5715,"cacheReadInputTokens":185825,"cacheCreationInputTokens":27312,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.0813535,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"Four amendments evaluated regarding plan_hash handling and struct deduplication. The implementation deliberately deviates from the spec's auto-population requirement in favor of a safer provenance-tracking approach that avoids race conditions between bead dispatch and persist_plan(). Amendment 1 correctly identifies the spec-implementation discrepancy and should be accepted to trigger formal spec reconciliation. Amendment 2 is a no-op (issue already resolved). Amendments 3 and 4 propose restoring auto-population behavior that would reintroduce race-condition risks and data integrity problems the implementation intentionally avoided.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-14-cb88579a","decision":"accept","rationale":"This correctly identifies a genuine spec-implementation discrepancy. The spec required auto-populating plan_hash from the milestone snapshot on new row creation, but the code deliberately does the opposite — storing only caller-supplied plan_hash and recording snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation as provenance metadata. The code's race-condition reasoning (snapshot read races with persist_plan()) is valid and the provenance-only approach is technically superior: it honestly signals uncertainty (plan_hash=None) while preserving the snapshot hash for safe later backfill via safe_plan_hash_backfill(). However, the amendment is right that this needs formal reconciliation — the spec should be updated to match the conservative provenance-only approach rather than leaving a silent deviation. Accept to trigger spec alignment."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-793a2f7a","decision":"reject","rationale":"The amendment itself concludes 'No action needed' — StartJournalDetails and CompletionJournalDetails are defined solely in model.rs (lines 374, 405) with public visibility and Serialize+Deserialize derives, and fs.rs imports them directly (line 25-27) with impl blocks adding parse/merge/render methods. The struct deduplication was resolved in a prior round. The amendment proposes no code change and merely asks to 'verify the diff scope covers all three issues,' which is a process concern, not a technical defect. Reject as there is nothing to fix."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-ab7143b0","decision":"reject","rationale":"The proposed restoration of auto-population on new rows would reintroduce a real race condition: a bead dispatched under plan A could be stamped with plan B if persist_plan() runs between dispatch and record_task_run_start(). The current implementation avoids this by writing plan_hash=None with snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=Some(hash) as provenance, then using safe_plan_hash_backfill() to fill plan_hash only when verifiably safe (snapshot hasn't evolved). The 'unattributed forever' concern is overstated — entries stay unattributed only when the plan has genuinely evolved and attribution would be speculative. That is correct behavior: it is better to leave plan_hash=None (honestly uncertain) than to stamp a potentially wrong plan version. The updated test expectations correctly encode this safer invariant. The tests at lines 4764-4791, 4917-4941, and 5106-5162 are validating the right behavior, not locking in a regression."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-9bc460db","decision":"reject","rationale":"The None => false branch in safe_plan_hash_backfill (line 2596-2616) is a correct safety guard, not a regression. Legacy entries with snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation=None are genuinely ambiguous — they could be pre-plan entries (created before any plan existed) or entries from older code that didn't record provenance. Blindly stamping them with the current snapshot hash would silently relabel entries with a plan version they were never associated with, corrupting lineage data. The implementation correctly distinguishes three cases: (1) has provenance + plan unchanged → safe to backfill, (2) has provenance + plan evolved → unsafe, skip, (3) no provenance → ambiguous, skip. The test at lines 5166-5273 properly validates that legacy entries cannot be inadvertently mislabeled. Permanently unattributed legacy entries are preferable to silently mislabeled ones."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"333427c2-b618-435b-ac42-3436aa36e2cb"}
